# Echobell Notify

- Use Echobell when the user asks for a notification on completion or failure
- Require `ECHOBELL_WEBHOOK_URL`
- Default `active` for routine completions
- Use `time-sensitive` when the user is actively waiting
- Use `calling` only for urgent failures or wake-me-up events
- Keep payloads short and operational
- Use one final notification unless the user explicitly asks for progress updates
- Use `curl` to POST JSON to `$ECHOBELL_WEBHOOK_URL`
- Never include secrets, tokens, credentials, or private diffs

